<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="interrupt-v">interrupt <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌɪntə'rʌpt/    美 /ˌɪntə'rʌpt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>打断；打扰：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don't interrupt the speaker; ask your questions afterwards.
不要打断演讲者，等他讲完你再提问。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I'm sorry to interrupt, but there's something important I have to tell you.
抱歉打扰一下，我有要事相告。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>中断；阻断：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Traffic was interrupted by floods. 
交通被洪水阻断。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>interruption /ˌɪntə'rʌpʃn/ n [U] &amp; [C]   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Will you stop <strong><em>_</em></strong> (打断) me when I’m talking?  （2012 全国）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. interrupting  </p></div>